</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B925B06F766B127B182FE9031104120" blockId="19.[151,1437,223,1258]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">
STATUS REFERENCE: The historical taxonomy is tangled. The species was initially described as 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F766B127B441FE9033B842EF" authority="Vieillot, 1816" authorityName="Vieillot" authorityYear="1816" class="Aves" family="Alaudidae" genus="Alauda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rufopilea">
<emphasis id="B9598714F766B127B441FE9032EB42EF" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">Alauda rufopilea</emphasis>
Vieillot, 1816
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F766B127B0CBFE6C300242EF" author="Sclater, W. L." box="[398,571,403,429]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" refId="ref29604" refString="Sclater, W. L. (1930) s. n. In: Systema Avium Aethiopicarum: a Systematic List of the Birds of the Ethiopian Region. Part 2. Taylor &amp; Francis for the British Ornithologists' Union, London, pp. i - xi + 305 - 922." type="book" year="1930">Sclater (1930)</bibRefCitation>
: 312–313 included 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F766B127B263FE6C31AB42EF" authorityName="Vieillot" authorityYear="1816" box="[806,914,403,429]" class="Aves" family="Alaudidae" genus="Alauda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rufopilea">
<emphasis id="B9598714F766B127B263FE6C31AB42EF" box="[806,914,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">rufopilea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F766B127B53CFE6C32D94290" authority="(Vieillot, 1816)" baseAuthorityName="Vieillot" baseAuthorityYear="1816" class="Aves" family="Alaudidae" genus="Mirafra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="apiata">
<emphasis id="B9598714F766B127B53CFE6C371342EF" box="[1145,1322,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">Mirafra apiata</emphasis>
(Vieillot, 1816)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F766B127B1AEFE4733FA4290" author="Peters, J. L." box="[235,451,439,466]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" refId="ref29365" refString="Peters, J. L. (1960 a) Family Alaudidae. In: Mayr, E. &amp; Greenway Jr., J. C. (Eds.), Check-List of Birds of the World. Vol. 9. Museum of Comparative Zoology, Cambridge, Massachusetts, pp. 3 - 80." type="book" year="1960">Peters (1960a: 16)</bibRefCitation>
did not recognise 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F766B127B3D8FE4831284293" baseAuthorityName="Sundevall" baseAuthorityYear="1850" box="[669,785,439,465]" class="Aves" family="Alaudidae" genus="Mirafra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fasciolata">
<emphasis id="B9598714F766B127B3D8FE4831284293" box="[669,785,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">fasciolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and noted that it was synonymous with 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F766B127B5A9FE48334142B4" authority="(Vieillot)" baseAuthorityName="Vieillot" class="Aves" family="Alaudidae" genus="Mirafra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="apiata" subSpecies="rufopilea">
<emphasis id="B9598714F766B127B5A9FE48333A42B7" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">Mirafra apiata rufopilea</emphasis>
(Vieillot)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F766B127B0C6FE24300142B7" author="White, C. M. N." box="[387,568,475,501]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" refId="ref30644" refString="White, C. M. N. (1961) A Revised Check List of African Broadbills, Pittas, Larks, Swallows, Wagtails and Pipits. Government Printer, Lusaka, 84 pp." type="book" year="1961">White 1961: 17</bibRefCitation>
did not recognise 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F766B127B24AFE2431BA42B7" baseAuthorityName="Sundevall" baseAuthorityYear="1850" box="[783,899,475,501]" class="Aves" family="Alaudidae" genus="Mirafra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fasciolata">
<emphasis id="B9598714F766B127B24AFE2431BA42B7" box="[783,899,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">fasciolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and considered 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F766B127B50DFE24368D42B7" authorityName="Vieillot" authorityYear="1816" box="[1096,1204,475,501]" class="Aves" family="Alaudidae" genus="Alauda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rufopilea">
<emphasis id="B9598714F766B127B50DFE24368D42B7" box="[1096,1204,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">rufopilea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be indeterminate within 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F766B127B1ACFE0030974158" authority="(Roberts, 1926)" baseAuthorityName="Roberts" baseAuthorityYear="1926" box="[233,686,511,538]" class="Aves" family="Alaudidae" genus="Mirafra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="apiata" subSpecies="hewitti">
<emphasis id="B9598714F766B127B1ACFE0033D4415B" box="[233,493,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">Mirafra apiata hewitti</emphasis>
(Roberts, 1926)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F766B127B3FDFE0031D1415B" author="Clancey, P. A." box="[696,1000,511,538]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" refId="ref28257" refString="Clancey, P. A. (1980) S. A. O. S. Checklist of Southern African Birds. Pretoria, South African Ornithological Society, 325 pp." type="book" year="1980">Clancey et al. (1980: 140)</bibRefCitation>
recognised 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F766B127B531FE003319417C" authority="(Sundevall)" baseAuthorityName="Sundevall" class="Aves" family="Alaudidae" genus="Mirafra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="apiata" subSpecies="fasciolata">
<emphasis id="B9598714F766B127B531FE0037A5415B" box="[1140,1436,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">Mirafra apiata fasciolata</emphasis>
(Sundevall)
</taxonomicName>
and included 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F766B127B08DFDDC3146417F" authority="Roberts, 1926" authorityName="Roberts" authorityYear="1926" box="[456,895,547,573]" class="Aves" family="Alaudidae" genus="Megalophonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hewitti">
<emphasis id="B9598714F766B127B08DFDDC30F6417F" box="[456,719,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">Megalophonus hewitti</emphasis>
Roberts, 1926
</taxonomicName>
, within this taxon. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F766B127B527FDDC37A1417F" author="Keith, S. &amp; Urban, E. K. &amp; Fry, C. H." box="[1122,1432,547,574]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" refId="ref29021" refString="Keith, S., Urban, E. K. &amp; Fry, C. H. (Eds.), (1992) The Birds of Africa. Vol. 4 [Broadbills to Thrushes]. Academic Press, London, 15 + 609 pp., 32 pls." type="book" year="1992">Keith et al. (1992: 30–31)</bibRefCitation>
, recognised 
<emphasis id="B9598714F766B127B05BFDB7338B4123" box="[286,434,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">
M. a. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F766B127B027FDB8338B4123" authorityName="Roberts" authorityYear="1926" box="[354,434,583,609]" class="Aves" family="Alaudidae" genus="Megalophonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hewitti">hewitti</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, but not 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F766B127B35EFDB830BE4123" authorityName="Vieillot" authorityYear="1816" box="[539,647,583,609]" class="Aves" family="Alaudidae" genus="Alauda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rufopilea">
<emphasis id="B9598714F766B127B35EFDB830BE4123" box="[539,647,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">rufopilea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F766B127B3EBFDB8311B4123" baseAuthorityName="Sundevall" baseAuthorityYear="1850" box="[686,802,583,609]" class="Aves" family="Alaudidae" genus="Mirafra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fasciolata">
<emphasis id="B9598714F766B127B3EBFDB8311B4123" box="[686,802,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">fasciolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C337088DF766B127B182FD93314F40E7" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8B925B06F766B127B182FD9331A040C0" blockId="19.[151,1437,223,1258]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">
<collectionCode id="ED3CC3C3F766B127B182FD9332C241C1" box="[199,251,620,646]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">TYPE</collectionCode>
MATERIAL: 
<collectorName id="26D83ED0F766B127B03DFD93307941C7" box="[376,576,619,646]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">From Sundevall’s</collectorName>
original description (1850: 99–100) it is apparent that the name is based on the figure in 
<collectorName id="26D83ED0F766B127B06BFD70334841EB" box="[302,369,655,681]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">Smith</collectorName>
(1849: 
<collectorName id="26D83ED0F766B127B088FD70303C41EB" box="[461,517,655,681]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">Plate</collectorName>
110, 
<figureCitation id="13164783F766B127B302FD70309241EB" box="[583,683,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="11.[151,250,514,538]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,306,487]" captionTargetId="figure-76@11.[151,1436,306,487]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 2. Sundevall’s personal acquisition catalogue, in which he recorded the date of the lectotype of Megalaema bilineata Sundevall as 4 November 1842." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6541741" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6541741/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">Figure 2</figureCitation>
). 
<collectorName id="26D83ED0F766B127B384FD6F31B341EB" box="[705,906,655,682]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">From Sundevall’s</collectorName>
acquisition catalogue he clearly also had 
<specimenCount id="9D2B908FF766B127B42BFD703335418F" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" type="generic">four specimens</specimenCount>
collected by 
<collectorName id="26D83ED0F766B127B0E1FD4C3029418F" box="[420,528,691,717]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">Wahlberg</collectorName>
available. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F766B127B3CEFD4C31A7418C" author="Gyldenstolpe, N." box="[651,926,691,718]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" pagination="1 - 116" refId="ref28755" refString="Gyldenstolpe, N. (1926) Types of birds in the Royal Natural History Museum in Stockholm. Arkiv f or Zoologi, 19, 1 - 116." type="journal article" year="1926">Gyldenstolpe (1926: 25)</bibRefCitation>
referred to NRM 569760 [6461] as a “type”, which we treat as a 
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F766B127B033FD2833E441B3" box="[374,477,727,753]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation of this adult male collected 
<date id="FF937DC6F766B127B2E6FD28367E41B3" box="[931,1095,727,754]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" value="1843-08-05">
<collectingDate id="EFD7842EF766B127B2E6FD28367E41B3" box="[931,1095,727,754]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" value="1843-08-05">5 August 1843</collectingDate>
</date>
north of 
<collectingCounty id="62F3238AF766B127B5EBFD28376741B3" box="[1198,1374,727,753]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">Vaal River. The</collectingCounty>
<specimenCount id="9D2B908FF766B127B421FD2833004057" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" type="generic" typeStatus="paralectotypes">three paralectotypes</specimenCount>
include: a juvenile male [6460], data unknown (most probably lost); an adult male [6462] collected in “Caffraria” (if the date is correct, then the bird was collected at the 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BF6C17CF766B127B2E9FCDF31E14078" box="[940,984,800,826]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">Eye</collectingMunicipality>
of the 
<location id="8EF20DDDF766B127B560FCE036934078" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:0384EA10F766B120B1D2FF68339B42CB:8EF20DDDF766B127B560FCE036934078" box="[1061,1194,799,826]" county="Vaal River. The" municipality="Eye" name="Mooi River" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" stateProvince="Berlin">Mooi River</location>
), 
<date id="FF937DC6F766B127B5FBFCE037AE407B" box="[1214,1431,799,825]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" value="1841-11-12">
<collectingDate id="EFD7842EF766B127B5FBFCE037AE407B" box="[1214,1431,799,825]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" value="1841-11-12">12 November 1841</collectingDate>
</date>
, exchanged to 
<location id="8EF20DDDF766B127B074FCBC3346401F" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:0384EA10F766B120B1D2FF68339B42CB:8EF20DDDF766B127B074FCBC3346401F" box="[305,383,835,861]" county="Vaal River. The" municipality="Eye" name="Leiden" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" stateProvince="Berlin">Leiden</location>
in 1850; and 
<specimenCount id="9D2B908FF766B127B350FCBB3042401F" box="[533,635,835,862]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" type="adult">one adult</specimenCount>
male [6463] collected at the 
<location id="8EF20DDDF766B127B2F9FCBB31D1401C" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:0384EA10F766B120B1D2FF68339B42CB:8EF20DDDF766B127B2F9FCBB31D1401C" box="[956,1000,836,862]" county="Vaal River. The" municipality="Eye" name="Eye" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" stateProvince="Berlin">Eye</location>
of the 
<location id="8EF20DDDF766B127B576FCBC368F401F" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:0384EA10F766B120B1D2FF68339B42CB:8EF20DDDF766B127B576FCBC368F401F" box="[1075,1206,835,861]" county="Vaal River. The" municipality="Eye" name="Mooi River" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" stateProvince="Berlin">Mooi River</location>
, 
<date id="FF937DC6F766B127B585FCBC37AE401F" box="[1216,1431,835,861]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" value="1841-11-12">
<collectingDate id="EFD7842EF766B127B585FCBC37AE401F" box="[1216,1431,835,861]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" value="1841-11-12">12 November 1841</collectingDate>
</date>
, exchanged with 
<collectingRegion id="49E995E4F766B127B009FC9833AB40C3" box="[332,402,871,897]" country="Germany" name="Berlin" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">Berlin</collectingRegion>
in 1853 (but no longer in the ZMB collection).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B925B06F766B127B182FC73314F40E7" blockId="19.[151,1437,223,1258]" box="[199,886,907,934]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">
