</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C337088DF766B127B182FC5030BC47AB" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B925B06F766B127B182FC5030BC47AB" blockId="19.[151,1437,223,1258]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">
COMMENTS: The TL was restricted to north of Potchefstroom by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F766B127B2E6FC5036B2408B" author="Gyldenstolpe, N." box="[931,1163,943,969]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" pagination="264 - 292" refId="ref28785" refString="Gyldenstolpe, N. (1934) The travels and collections of Johan August Wahlberg, 1810 - 1856: a pioneer naturalist in South Africa. Ibis, 76, 264 - 292. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1474 - 919 X. 1934. tb 01567. x" type="journal article" year="1934">Gyldenstolpe (1934)</bibRefCitation>
but is imprecise. Wahlberg’s entries for the period 
<date id="FF937DC6F766B127B09AFC2C30D040AF" box="[479,745,979,1005]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" value="1843-07-24" valueMax="1843-08-09" valueMin="1843-07-24">24 July–9 August 1843</date>
are vague regarding localities. He noted that he crossed the Vaal River (probably at Skandinawiedrif at 
<geoCoordinate id="EE193DC1F766B127B3C5FC0831214753" box="[640,792,1015,1042]" degrees="26" direction="south" minutes="56" orientation="latitude" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" precision="925" value="-26.933332">26° 56’ south</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE193DC1F766B127B266FC0831904750" box="[803,937,1015,1042]" degrees="27" direction="east" minutes="03" orientation="longitude" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" precision="925" value="27.05">27° 03’ east</geoCoordinate>
) on 28 July, and that he continued travelling north. On 1–3 August, no locality is given but his activity is given as “resting”. On 4 August he continued travelling, spending a few days at Potchefstroom on the way, arriving at the Eye of the Mooi River (
<geoCoordinate id="EE193DC1F766B127B5EFFBC03778471B" box="[1194,1345,1087,1113]" degrees="26" direction="south" minutes="12" orientation="latitude" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" precision="925" value="-26.2">26° 12’ south</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE193DC1F766B127B409FBC032FF473C" degrees="27" direction="east" minutes="10" orientation="longitude" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" precision="925" value="27.166666">27° 10’ east</geoCoordinate>
), on 9 August. Specimen label localities show that he collected at the Mooi River, or Mooi River Dorp as it was known at the time (= Potchefstroom, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE193DC1F766B127B373FB7830F547E3" box="[566,716,1159,1185]" degrees="26" direction="south" minutes="40" orientation="latitude" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" precision="925" value="-26.666666">26° 40’ south</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE193DC1F766B127B39DFB78316547E0" box="[728,860,1159,1186]" degrees="27" direction="east" minutes="05" orientation="longitude" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" precision="925" value="27.083334">27° 05’ east</geoCoordinate>
) on 4, 7, and 
<date id="FF937DC6F766B127B2B6FB7836A147E3" box="[1011,1176,1159,1185]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" value="1843-08-08">8 August 1843</date>
, and from 9–28 August collected at the Eye of the Mooi River. The 
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F766B127B3C2FB5430D74787" box="[647,750,1195,1221]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F766B127B251FB5431E34787" authorityName="Sundevall" authorityYear="1850" box="[788,986,1195,1221]" class="Aves" family="Alaudidae" genus="Alauda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fasciolata">
<emphasis id="B9598714F766B127B251FB5431E34787" box="[788,986,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">Alauda fasciolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, collected on 5 August, must have been collected at, or very close to Potchefstroom.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
