<subSubSection id="C337088DF766B120B182FA33316B425F" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="541" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8B925B06F766B120B182FA3330E743BB" blockId="19.[151,1437,1411,2014]" lastBlockId="20.[151,1437,150,393]" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="541" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">
<collectionCode id="ED3CC3C3F766B127B182FA3332C246A1" box="[199,251,1484,1510]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">TYPE</collectionCode>
MATERIAL: Gyldenstolpe referred for a description of the new nominal species to “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F766B127B53BFA34376C46A7" box="[1150,1365,1483,1509]" class="Aves" family="Alaudidae" genus="Mirafra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fringillaris">
<emphasis id="B9598714F766B127B53BFA34376C46A7" box="[1150,1365,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">Mirafra fringillaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
auct.” published by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F766B127B06CFA1030104548" author="Sharpe, R. B." box="[297,553,1519,1546]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" pagination="614 - 651" refId="ref29658" refString="Sharpe, R. B. (1874) A study of the larks of Southern Africa. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 1874, 614 - 651. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1874. tb 02519. x" type="journal article" year="1874">Sharpe, 1874: 649–650</bibRefCitation>
+ plate 75. Gyldenstolpe also stated: “As type for 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F766B127B515FA103725454B" authorityName="Gyldenstolpe" authorityYear="1926" box="[1104,1308,1519,1545]" class="Aves" family="Alaudidae" genus="Mirafra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="passerina">
<emphasis id="B9598714F766B127B515FA103725454B" box="[1104,1308,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">Mirafra passerina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
I designate one of our specimens, viz.: 
<emphasis id="B9598714F766B127B08EF9EB33C6456F" box="[459,511,1556,1581]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">Type</emphasis>
: 
<specimenCount id="9D2B908FF766B127B34BF9EB301A456C" box="[526,547,1556,1582]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
ad., Mohoapoani, No. 6457”. Sharpe based his description on 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F766B127B59AF9EC328A4513" author="Sundevall, C. J." pageId="19" pageNumber="540" pagination="96 - 111" refId="ref29984" refString="Sundevall, C. J. (1850) Foglar fran sodra Afrika. Ofversigt af Kongliga Vetenskaps-akademiens forhandlingar, 7 (4), 96 - 111." type="journal article" year="1850">Sundevall, 1850: 99</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F766B127B1A8F9C833924513" author="Gray, G. R." box="[237,427,1591,1617]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" refId="ref28673" refString="Gray, G. R. (1870) Hand-list of Genera and Species of Birds, Distinguishing those Contained in the British Museum. Part 2. Conirostres, Scansores, Columbae, and Gallinae. Trustees of the British Museum, London, 278 pp." type="book" year="1870">Gray (1870: 121</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F766B127B0FCF9C830B64513" box="[441,655,1591,1617]" class="Aves" family="Alaudidae" genus="Mirafra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="occipitalis">
<emphasis id="B9598714F766B127B0FCF9C830B64513" box="[441,655,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">Mirafra occipitalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (which seems to be an erroneous reference back to Sundevall), and five additional specimens at Sharpe’s disposal. The type series consists of at least one (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F766B127B510F9A436DF4537" author="Sharpe, R. B." box="[1109,1254,1627,1653]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" pagination="614 - 651" refId="ref29658" refString="Sharpe, R. B. (1874) A study of the larks of Southern Africa. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 1874, 614 - 651. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1874. tb 02519. x" type="journal article" year="1874">Sharpe 1874</bibRefCitation>
, Plate 75, figure 1) of Sharpe’s 
<specimenCount id="9D2B908FF766B127B07AF98033DE45DB" box="[319,487,1663,1689]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" type="generic">five specimens</specimenCount>
plus three of 
<specimenCount id="9D2B908FF766B127B3C0F980310845DB" box="[645,817,1663,1689]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" type="generic">four specimens</specimenCount>
on which Sundevall based his report (one was sent on exchange to Leiden in 1850, and it is unlikely that Gyldenstolpe had seen it). The 
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F766B127B56FF95C36B545FF" box="[1066,1164,1699,1725]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">holotype</typeStatus>
is NRM569762 [6457], a study skin of an adult male collected 
<date id="FF937DC6F766B127B308F937312E45A3" box="[589,791,1735,1762]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" value="1843-11-07">
7 November 
<quantity id="4CD5F6E3F766B127B39AF938312E45A3" box="[735,791,1735,1761]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.68122" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" unit="in" value="1843.0">1843</quantity>
</date>
in Saulspoort. 
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F766B127B284F937361745A0" box="[961,1070,1736,1762]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">Paratypes</typeStatus>
are probably the additional ones mentioned: NRM 569763 [6458], a male collected 
<date id="FF937DC6F766B127B38FF91431B84447" box="[714,897,1771,1798]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" value="1842-01-22">22 January 1842</date>
at Apies River; NRM 537998 [6459], a mounted male collected 
<date id="FF937DC6F766B127B000F8EF302D446B" box="[325,532,1807,1834]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" value="1843-11-07">7 November 1843</date>
at Thabazimbi (labelled Thabazimbi Mohapoani); and the specimen figured in Plate 75. However, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F766B127B036F8CC3082440F" author="Grant, C. H. B. &amp; Praed, C. W. M." box="[371,699,1843,1869]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" pagination="30 - 31" refId="ref28552" refString="Grant, C. H. B. &amp; Praed, C. W. M. (1949) Notes on eastern and southern African birds. (2) On Mirafra passerina Gyldenstolpe. Bulletin of the British Ornithologists' Club, 69, 30 - 31." type="journal article" year="1949">Grant &amp; Praed (1949: 30–31)</bibRefCitation>
have pointed out that Gyldenstolpe had given a nom. nov. for 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F766B127B431F8CB33684433" class="Aves" family="Alaudidae" genus="Mirafra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fringillaris">
<emphasis id="B9598714F766B127B431F8CB33684433" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">Mirafra fringillaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
auct., not 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F766B127B08DF8A831294433" authority="Sundevall" authorityName="Sundevall" authorityYear="1850" box="[456,784,1879,1905]" class="Aves" family="Alaudidae" genus="Alauda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fringillaris">
<emphasis id="B9598714F766B127B08DF8A830A04433" box="[456,665,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">Alauda fringillaris</emphasis>
Sundevall
</taxonomicName>
(Öfvers. K. Sv. Vet. Akad. Förhandl., Band 7, No. 4, 
<date id="FF937DC6F766B127B42FF8A8332D44D4" pageId="19" pageNumber="540" value="1850-04-17">17th April 1850</date>
, p. 99). Gyldenstolpe’s name is therefore a new specific name and not a nom. nov. Sharpe’s description (1874) was based on a type series of five birds. A careful examination of the specimens in the type series identified one that must have been the 
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F766B127B099F83C3078449F" box="[476,577,1987,2013]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">holotype</typeStatus>
, and therefore Gyldenstolpe’s 
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F766B127B2DFF83C31C5449F" box="[922,1020,1987,2013]" pageId="19" pageNumber="540">holotype</typeStatus>
and type locality can have no standing. Based on what is published by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F761B120B36EFF68310043F3" author="Sharpe, R. B." box="[555,825,150,177]" pageId="20" pageNumber="541" pagination="614 - 651" refId="ref29658" refString="Sharpe, R. B. (1874) A study of the larks of Southern Africa. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 1874, 614 - 651. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1874. tb 02519. x" type="journal article" year="1874">Sharpe (1874: 649-650)</bibRefCitation>
the type specimen may be NHMUK 1889.9.13.167, a study skin of a male collected 
<date id="FF937DC6F761B120B0A8FF4430FF4397" box="[493,710,187,213]" pageId="20" pageNumber="541" value="1873-11-29">
29 November 
<quantity id="4CD5F6E3F761B120B3CBFF4430FF4397" box="[654,710,187,213]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.75742" pageId="20" pageNumber="541" unit="in" value="1873.0">1873</quantity>
</date>
in Transvaal by T.E. Buckley but may as well be one of the 
<specimenCount id="9D2B908FF761B120B42BFF44333543BB" pageId="20" pageNumber="541" type="generic">four specimens</specimenCount>
collected by C. J. Andersson in 
<collectingCountry id="F33A1B96F761B120B330FF2030E043BB" box="[629,729,223,249]" name="Namibia" pageId="20" pageNumber="541">Namibia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B925B06F761B120B182FEFC316B425F" blockId="20.[151,1437,150,393]" box="[199,850,259,285]" pageId="20" pageNumber="541">
